{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarUI"},{"text":" provides presentation-only calendar components for record-based apps. Host apps pass records, display configuration, selection state, and callbacks while keeping storage and detail navigation outside the package.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this package when you need a reusable week\/month calendar with a selected-day list and swipe-to-delete behavior, but each app needs different record values, text formatting, and detail screens.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration.rowHeight","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" controls the minimum selected-day row card height. "},{"code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration.rowSpacing","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" controls the vertical spacing between selected-day rows, defaults to 5 points, can be customized by host apps, and clamps negative values to zero. Values below "},{"code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration<YourRecord>.minimumRowHeight","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", currently 44 points, are clamped so row content keeps a standard touch target. Row spacing does not reduce the configured row height. "},{"code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration<YourRecord>.minimumRowHeight(forRowSpacing:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" remains as a deprecated compatibility helper; use "},{"code":"minimumRowHeight","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for new code."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration.theme"},{"text":" accepts semantic colors through ","type":"text"},{"code":"RecordsCalendarTheme","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", including the full-page background, calendar and record container background, primary and secondary content colors, and independent light and dark summary tile backgrounds. The default "},{"code":".standard","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" theme preserves the system grouped page background, material calendar container, grouped record containers, and existing green appearance. Host apps can supply adaptive SwiftUI colors without changing package internals."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Theme initialization without an explicit light-mode secondary content color remains supported and derives that color from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"contentColor"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To change only surfaces, copy ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".standard"},{"text":" and set ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"backgroundColor"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"containerBackgroundColor"},{"type":"text","text":". The package applies the container color consistently to the calendar, selected-day empty state, and record rows."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Calendar day buttons can receive an accessibility label and value from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarConfiguration"},{"text":". The package passes a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RecordsCalendarDayAccessibilityContext"},{"text":" with the date, its display calendar, and the today, selected, and has-records states so host apps can provide their own localized full-date label and state text. Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context.calendar"},{"type":"text","text":" when formatting the date so its locale and time zone stay consistent with the visible calendar. When these closures are omitted, the package preserves SwiftUI’s default day-number announcement. Selected dates also use the system selected accessibility trait."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"collection","symbolKind":"module","modules":[{"name":"RecordsCalendarUI"}],"title":"RecordsCalendarUI","roleHeading":"Framework","externalID":"RecordsCalendarUI"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/recordscalendarui"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Reusable SwiftUI calendar records UI for apps that own their own data, persistence, and navigation.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarView","doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarConfiguration","doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarTheme","doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarDisplayScope"],"title":"Calendar Presentation","anchor":"Calendar-Presentation"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarEntry"],"title":"Record Model Boundary","anchor":"Record-Model-Boundary"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarBestValueComparator","doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/RecordsCalendarDayAccessibilityContext"],"title":"Structures","generated":true,"anchor":"Structures"}],"references":{"doc://recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI/documentation/RecordsCalendarUI/RecordsCalendarBestValueComparator":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"title":"RecordsCalendarBestValueComparator","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"RecordsCalendarBestValueComparator","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/recordscalendarui.RecordsCalendarUI\/documentation\/RecordsCalendarUI\/R